[SN]TITLE[SN]
Laura Daniels: Welsh bowls player takes British Isles singles title

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Welsh bowls player Laura Daniels continued her preparations for the 2018 Commonwealth Games in Australia by winning the British Isles singles title on Saturday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Daniels had to come from behind to beat Bernie O'Neill 21-19 in the final at Llandrindod Wells, having trailed the Irish player 18-9 at one point.
Wales' Alis Butten and Anwen Butten had to settle for silver in the pairs.
The duo lost 25-13 to England's Sophie Tolchard and Natalie Chestney.
